heng]]\n|-\n|[[Chen Meng-tsung]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n|[[National Hsin-Feng Senior High School|Hsin Feng]]\n|-\n|}\n\n== Awards ==\n* Best coach: [[Chen Jiunn-ming]] ([[National Pei Men Senior High School|Pei Men]])\n* Best player: [[Yang Chao-hsun]] ([[National Pei Men Senior High School|Pei Men]])\n* Golden shoe: [[Wu Pai-ho]] ([[National Pei Men Senior High School|Pei Men]]) <ref name=\"goldenshoe\">According to league regulation, the Golden Shoe candidate should come from teams of top four places. As a result, though [[Chung Cheng Industrial Vocational High School|Chung Cheng]] striker [[Chen Po-liang]] scored the most goals in the league season, the Golden Shoe award was given to [[Wu Pai-ho]] of [[National Pei Men Senior High School]].</ref>\n\n== Footnotes ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{in lang|zh}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20061216142235/http://www.ltsports.com.tw/HFL/default.asp Highschool Football League 2006]\n\n{{Highschool Football League}}\n\n[[Category:Highschool Football League seasons]]\n[[Category:2006 in Taiwanese football|2]]\n[[Category:2006\u201307 in Asian second tier association football leagues|Taiwan]]\n[[Category:2005\u201306 in Asian second tier association football leagues|Taiwan]]\n", "text_old": "The '''2006''' season of '''[[Highschool Football League]]''' began on February 16, 2006 and ended on May 25, 2006. [[National Pei Men Senior High School|National Pei Men Senior High School football team]] of [[Tainan County]] became the first champion of the league.\n\n== League table ==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n|sortable_table=y\n\n|team1=PMN|name_PMN=[[National Pei Men Senior High School|Pei Men]]\n|team2=SCH|name_SCH=[[National San Chung Senior High School|San Chung]]\n|team3=YIL|name_YIL=[[National Yilan Senior High School|Yilan]]\n|team4=HUA|name_HUA=[[National Hualien Senior High School|Hualien]]\n|team5=CCH|name_CCH=[[Chung Cheng Industrial Vocational High School|Chung Cheng]]\n|team6=HSF|name_HSF=[[National Hsin Feng Senior High School|Hsin Feng]]\n|team7=CSH|name_CSH=[[Chung Shan Industrial and Commercial School|Chung Shan]]\n|team8=TAI|name_TAI=[[Taibei High School|Taibei]]\n|win_PMN=8|draw_PMN=1|loss_PMN=1|gf_PMN=26|ga_PMN=7\n|win_SCH=6|draw_SCH=3|loss_SCH=1|gf_SCH=24|ga_SCH=14\n|win_YIL=6|draw_YIL=2|loss_YIL=2|gf_YIL=22|ga_YIL=8\n|win_HUA=4|draw_HUA=1|loss_HUA=5|gf_HUA=23|ga_HUA=18\n|win_CCH=4|draw_CCH=0|loss_CCH=6|gf_CCH=25|ga_CCH=38\n|win_HSF=3|draw_HSF=2|loss_HSF=5|gf_HSF=14|ga_HSF=15\n|win_CSH=1|draw_CSH=3|loss_CSH=6|gf_CSH=9|ga_CSH=24\n|win_TAI=1|draw_TAI=2|loss_TAI=7|gf_TAI=14|ga_TAI=33\n|update=complete|source=\n}}\n\n== Qualification ==\nThe top 4 teams of [[Chinese Taipei National Youth Cup]] 2005 season ([[National Yilan Senior High School|Yilan]], [[National Pei Men Senior High School|Pei Men]], [[National San Chung Senior High School|San Chung]], and [[National Hualien Senior High School|Hualien]]) were automatically granted to become the league members. The remaining 4 places were contested by [[Taipei County Ching Shui Senior High School|Ching Shui]], [[Chung Cheng Industrial Vocational High School|Chung Cheng]], [[Chung Shan Industrial and Commercial School|Chung Shan]], [[National Hsin Feng Senior High School|Hsin Feng]], [[National Hualien Vocational High School of Agriculture|Hualien Agriculture]], [[National Pingtung Senior High School|Pingtung]], and [[Taibei High School|Taibei]] though a qualification competition held on December 19 and 20, 2005.\n\nIn the qualification competition, the teams are placed in either group A or group B and play every team in their group once. The winner of each group qualifies for the 2006 season of the Highschool Football League while the second-placed team in each group plays the third-placed team in the other group in a playoff to determine the final two teams that qualify for the league.\n\n=== Group A ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!Team!!Pl