o.asp?waterxno=40 (Report)]\n}}\n\n== Top goalscorers ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|- \n!Player\n!Goals\n!Team\n|-\n|- \n|[[Chen Po-liang]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|11\n|[[Chung Cheng Industrial Vocational High School|Chung Cheng]]\n|- \n|[[Wu Pai-ho]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|10\n|[[National Pei Men Senior High School|Pei Men]]\n|-\n|[[Lo Chih-an]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|9\n|[[National I-Lan Senior High School|Ilan]]\n|-\n|[[Lin Ching-tsan]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|8\n|[[National Hualien Senior High School|Hualien]]\n|-\n|[[Tai Hung-hsu]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|6\n|[[National San Chung Senior High School|San Chung]]\n|-\n|[[Huang Wei]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n|[[National San Chung Senior High School|San Chung]]\n|-\n|[[Huang Kun-huang]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n|[[Taibei High School|Taibei]]\n|-\n|[[Lin Chia-ming]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n|[[Chung Cheng Industrial Vocational High School|Chung Cheng]]\n|-\n|[[Chan Che-yuan]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n|[[Chung Cheng Industrial Vocational High School|Chung Cheng]]\n|-\n|[[Chen Meng-tsung]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n|[[National Hsin-Feng Senior High School|Hsin Feng]]\n|-\n|}\n\n== Awards ==\n* Best coach: [[Chen Jiunn-ming]] ([[National Pei Men Senior High School|Pei Men]])\n* Best player: [[Yang Chao-hsun]] ([[National Pei Men Senior High School|Pei Men]])\n* Golden shoe: [[Wu Pai-ho]] ([[National Pei Men Senior High School|Pei Men]]) <ref name=\"goldenshoe\">According to league regulation, the Golden Shoe candidate should come from teams of top four places. As a result, though [[Chung Cheng Industrial Vocational High School|Chung Cheng]] striker [[Chen Po-liang]] scored the most goals in the league season, the Golden Shoe award was given to [[Wu Pai-ho]] of [[National Pei Men Senior High School]].</ref>\n\n== Footnotes ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{in lang|zh}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20061216142235/http://www.ltsports.com.tw/HFL/default.asp Highschool Football League 2006]\n\n{{Highschool Football League}}\n\n[[Category:Highschool Football League seasons]]\n[[Category:2006 in Taiwanese football|2]]\n[[Category:2006\u201307 in Asian second tier association football leagues|Taiwan]]\n[[Category:2005\u201306 in Asian second tier association football leagues|Taiwan]]\n", "name_user": "Frietjes", "label": "safe", "comment": "expand templates perFb team TfD outcomeandFb competition TfD outcomeandFb cl TfD outcomeandFb rbr TfD outcome", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2006_Highschool_Football_League"}
{"title_page": "George X of Kartli", "text_new": "{{Infobox royalty|monarch\n|name            = George X\n|title           = \n|image           = \n|image_size      = 255px\n|caption         = George X by [[Teramo Castelli]]\n|succession      = [[List of Georgian monarchs|King of Kartli]] \n|reign           = 1599\u20131606\n|coronation      = \n|predecessor     = [[Simon I of Kartli]]\n|successor       = [[Luarsab II of Kartli]]\n|spouse          = \n|issue           = [[Luarsab II of Kartli]]<br>[[Princess Elene of Kartli]]<br>[[Khorashan of Kartli]]\n|house           = [[Bagrationi dynasty]]\n|house-type      = Dynasty\n|father          = [[Simon I of Kartli]]\n|mother          = [[Nestan-Darejan of Kakheti, Queen of Kartli]]\n|birth_date      = 1560\n|birth_place     = \n|death_date      = 1606\n|death_place     = \n|place of burial = \n|religion        = [[Georgian Orthodox Church]]\n|}}\n'''George X''' ([[Georgian language|Georgian]]: \u10d2\u10d8\u10dd\u10e0\u10d2\u10d8 X, '''''Giorgi X''''') (c. 1561 \u2013 September 7, 1606), of the [[Bagrationi]] royal dynasty, was a king of the eastern [[Georgia (country)|Georgian]] kingdom of [[Kingdom of Kartli (1484-1762)|Kartli]] from 1599 until his death.\n==Life==\nGeorge was the eldest son of [[Simon I of Kartli]] and his wife, [[Nestan-Darejan of Kakheti, Queen of Kartli|Nestan-Darejan of Kakheti]]. George fought alongside his father against the [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] occupation forces since 1598. He held power after Simon was taken captive by the Turks at the [[Battle of Nakhiduri]] in 1599. George attempted several times, though vainly, to ransom his father (who would die as a prisoner in 1612) from captivity and even offered to the [[Sublime Porte]] his son as hostage. He soon returned to his struggle against the Ottomans and recovered [[Lori Province|Lorri]] in 1601. In 1602, when the [[Safavid dynasty|Safavid]] [[shah]] of [[Safavid Iran|Persia]] [[Abbas the Great|Abbas I]] resumed a war against the Ottomans, George sided with the Persians and led the Georgian auxiliary troops which took part in the conquest of [[Erivan]] in 1603/1604. As a reward, Abbas I granted Giorgi X a minor possession in [[Iran]]. In exchange, the shah asked for an area in the [[Debed River]] valley in the strategic Lorri district. Abbas I populated this territory with members of the [[Turkmen people|Turkmen]] tribe [[Borchali]]. Finally, the Shah permitted Giorgi X to return to Kartli.\n\nHe was the first king of Kartli who attempted to establish diplomatic ties with the northern co-religionist power of [[Muscovy]]. George decided even to give his daughter Elene to the [[Czar]] [[Boris Godunov]] in marriage. However, unstable political situation in both countries terminated these contacts.\n\nAccording to Georgian chronicles, George X died suddenly, from a sting on his tongue, after biting into a cake with a [[bee]] in it, at Mejvriskhevi, 1606. There have also been some speculations that the king was poisoned on the orders of the shah Abbas I.{{sfn|Floor|Herzig|2012|page=469}} He was buried at [[Mtskheta]].\n\n==Family==\nGeorge married on September 15, 1578, Mariam (Tamar) (died c. 1614), daughter of Giorgi I Lipartiani, of the [[Dadiani]] dynasty. Their children were:\n#[[Luarsab II of Kartli|Luarsab II]], King of Kartli.\n#David (born c. 1595), who disappeared while on a mission to rescue Simon I from the Turkish captivity. \n#[[Princess Elene of Kartli|Elene]], affianced to [[Feodor II of Russia]].\n#[[Khorashan of Kartli|Khorashan]] (died 1658), second wife of [[Teimuraz I of Kakheti]].\n#Tinatin (Lela; known as Fatma Sultan Begum and possibly as [[Gulchara]] in Iran) was given in marriage in 1604 to Shah Abbas I, who divorced her after the execution of her brother Luarsab II and married her of to [[Paykar Kh\u0101n Ig\u012brm\u012b D\u016brt]], Khan of Barda and governor of Kakheti (1620\u20131625).\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n* {{cite book|editor1-last=Floor|editor1-first=Willem|editor2-last=Herzig|editor2-first=Edmund|editor2-link=Edmund Herzig|title=Iran and the World in the Safavid Age|date=2012|publisher=I.B.Tauris|isbn=978-1850439301|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Mikaberidze|first1=Alexander|title=Historical Dictionary of Georgia|date=2015|publisher=Rowman & Littlefield|isbn=978-1442241466|page=335|edition=2}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070927105209/http://www.istoria.ge/personografia/G/giorgi%20X.htm Giorgi X (In Georgian)]\n*{{in lang|en}} Kings of Kartli at [http://www.4dw.net/royalark/Georgia/kartli.htm ''Royal Ark '' website]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{succession box | title= [[List of the Kings of Georgia|King of Kartli]]| before= [[Simon I of Kartli|Simon I]] | after= [[Luarsab II of Kartli|Luarsab II]] | years=1599\u20131606}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Triarchy in Georgia}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:George 10 Of Kartli}}\n[[Category:Kings of Kartli]]\n[[Category:Bagrationi dynasty of the Kingdom of Kartli]]\n[[Category:1560s births]]\n[[Category:1606 deaths]]\n[[Category:Eastern Orthodox monarchs]]\n[[Category:Burials at Svetitskhoveli Cathedral]]\n[[Category:16th-century people of the Safavid Empire]]\n[[Category:17th-century people of the Safavid Empire]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox royalty|monarch\n|name            = George X\n|title           = \n|image           = \n|image_size      = 255px\n|caption         = George X by [[Teramo Castelli]]\n|succession      = [[List of Georgian monarchs|King of Kartli]] \n|reign           = 1599\u20131606\n|coronation      = \n|predecessor     = [[Simon I of Kartli]]\n|successor       = [[Luarsab II of Kartli]]\n|spouse          = \n|issue           = [[Luarsab II of Kartli]]<br>[[Princess Elene of Kartli]]<br>[[Khorashan of Kartli]]\n|house           = [[Bagrationi dynasty]]\n|house-type      = Dynasty\n|father          = [[Simon I of Kartli]]\n|mother          = [[Nestan-Darejan of Kakheti, Queen of Kartli]]\n|birth_date      = 1560\n|birth_place     = \n|death_date      = 1606\n|death_place     = \n|place of burial = \n|religion        = [[Georgian Orthodox Church]]\n|}}\n'''George X''' ([[Georgian language|Georgian]]: \u10d2\u10d8\u10dd\u10e0\u10d2\u10d8 X, '''''Giorgi X''''') (c. 1561 \u2013 September 7, 1606), of the [[Bagrationi]] royal dynasty, was a king of the eastern [[Georgia (country)|Georgian]] kingdom of [[Kingdom of Kartli (1484-1762)|Kartli]] from 1599 until his death.\n==Life==\nGeorge was the eldest son of [[Simon I of Kartli]] and his wife, [[Nestan-Darejan of Kakheti, Queen of Kartli|Nestan-Darejan of Kakheti]]. George fought alongside his father against the [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] occupation forces since 1598. He held power after Simon was taken captive by the Turks at the [[Battle of Nakhiduri]] in 1599. George attempted several times, though vainly, to ransom his father (who would die as a prisoner in 1612) from captivity and even offered to the [[Sublime Porte]] his son as hostage. He soon returned to his struggle against the Ottomans and recovered [[Lori Province|Lorri]] in 1601. In 1602, when the [[Safavid dynasty|Safavid]] [[shah]] of [[Safavid Iran|Persia]] [[Abbas I the Great|Abbas I]] resumed a war against the Ottomans, George sided with the Persians and led the Georgian auxiliary troops which took part in the conquest of [[Erivan]] in 1603/1604. As a reward, Abbas I granted Giorgi X a minor possession in [[Iran]]. In exchange, the shah asked for an area in the [[Debed River]] valley in the strategic Lorri district. Abbas I populated this territory with members of the [[Turkmen people|Turkmen]] tribe [[Borchali]]. Finally, the Shah permitted Giorgi X to return to Kartli.\n\nHe was the first king of Kartli who attempted to establish diplomatic ties with the northern co-religionist power of [[Muscovy]]. George decided even to give his daughter Elene to the [[Czar]] [[Boris Godunov]] in marriage. However, unstable political situation in both countries terminated these contacts.\n\nAccording to Georgian chronicles, George X died suddenly, from a sting on his tongue, after biting into a cake with a [[bee]] in it, at Mejvriskhevi, 1606. There have also been some speculations that the king was poisoned on the orders of the shah Abbas I.{{sfn|Floor|Herzig|2012|page=469}} He was buried at [[Mtskheta]].\n\n==Family==\nGeorge married on September 15, 1578, Mariam (Tamar) (died c. 1614), daughter of Giorgi I Lipartiani, of the [[Dadiani]] dynasty. Their children were:\n#[[Luarsab II of Kartli|Luarsab II]], King of Kartli.\n#David (born c. 1595), who disappeared while on a mission to rescue Simon I from the Turkish captivity. \n#[[Princess Elene of Kartli|Elene]], affianced to [[Feodor II of Russia]].\n#[[Khorashan of Kartli|Khorashan]] (died 1658), second wife of [[Teimuraz I of Kakheti]].\n#Tinatin (Lela; known as Fatma Sultan Begum and possibly as [[Gulchara]] in Iran) was given in marriage in 1604 to Shah Abbas I, who divorced her after the execution of her brother Luarsab II and married her of to [[Paykar Kh\u0101n Ig\u012brm\u012b D\u016brt]], Khan of Barda and governor of Kakheti (1620\u20131625).\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n* {{cite book|editor1-last=Floor|editor1-first=Willem|editor2-last=Herzig|editor2-first=Edmund|editor2-link=Edmund Herzig|title=Iran and the World in the Safavid Age|date=2012|publisher=I.B.Tauris|isbn=978-1850439301|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Mikaberidze|first1=Alexander|title=Historical Dictionary of Georgia|date=2015|publisher=Rowman & Littlefield|isbn=978-1442241466|page=335|edition=2}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070927105209/http://www.istoria.ge/personografia/G/giorgi%20X.htm Giorgi X (In Georgian)]\n*{{in lang|en}} Kings of Kartli at [http://www.4dw.net/royalark/Georgia/kartli.htm ''Royal Ark '' website]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{succession box | title= [[List of the Kings of Georgia|King of Kartli]]| before= [[Simon I of Kartli|Simon I]] | after= [[Luarsab II of Kartli|Luarsab II]] | years=1599\u