{"title_page": "Torin Dorn", "text_new": "{{Infobox NFL biography\n|image=\n|alt=\n|caption=\n|number=46\n|position=[[Cornerback]]\n|birth_date={{birth date and age|1968|2|29}}\n|birth_place=[[Greenwood, South Carolina]]\n|height_ft = 6\n|height_in = 0\n|weight_lbs = 200\n|high_school = [[Southfield High School|Southfield]]<br>([[Southfield, Michigan]])\n|college= [[North Carolina Tar Heels football|North Carolina]]\n|draftyear=1990\n|draftround=4\n|draftpick=95\n|undraftedyear=\n|pastteams=\n* [[History of the Oakland Raiders|Los Angeles Raiders]] (1990\u20131994)\n* [[St. Louis Rams]] (1995\u20131996)\n|statlabel1=Games played\n|statvalue1=84\n|statlabel2= Games [[Starting lineup|started]]\n|statvalue2=4\n|statlabel3= [[Fumble]] recoveries\n|statvalue3=2\n|statlabel4= [[Interception]]s\n|statvalue4=3\n|statlabel5=[[Touchdown]]s\n|statvalue5=\n|nfl=DOR155733\n|pfr=DornTo20\n}}\n\n'''Torin Damon Dorn Sr.''' (born February 29, 1968) is a former professional [[American football]] [[cornerback]] in the  [[National Football League]]. He played seven seasons for the [[History of the Oakland Raiders|Los Angeles Raiders]] (1990\u20131994) and the [[St. Louis Rams]] (1995\u20131996). Dorn Sr. played college football for [[University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill]] from 1986-1989 where he played both running back and defensive back. Initially Dorn Sr. played running back for the first three seasons, and then played defensive back as a senior. \n\nHis son Torin Dorn Jr. plays [[basketball]] for the [[NC State Wolfpack men's basketball team]] after transferring from the [[UNC Charlotte 49ers men's basketball|Charlotte 49ers]] following his freshman season.<ref>{{cite web |title=Torin Dorn - 2017-18 - Men's Basketball |url=https://gopack.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=5007 |website=NC State University Athletics |accessdate=9 February 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n{{Raiders1990DraftPicks}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dorn, Torin}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Greenwood, South Carolina]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Southfield, Michigan]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Michigan]]\n[[Category:American football cornerbacks]]\n[[Category:North Carolina Tar Heels football players]]\n[[Category:Los Angeles Raiders players]]\n[[Category:St. Louis Rams players]]\n\n\n{{defensiveback-1960s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox NFL biography\n|image=\n|alt=\n|caption=\n|number=46\n|position=[[Cornerback]]\n|birth_date={{birth date and age|1968|2|29}}\n|birth_place=[[Greenwood, South Carolina]]\n|height_ft = 6\n|height_in = 0\n|weight_lbs = 200\n|high_school = [[Southfield High School|Southfield]]<br>([[Southfield, Michigan]])\n|college= [[North Carolina Tar Heels football|North Carolina]]\n|draftyear=1990\n|draftround=4\n|draftpick=95\n|undraftedyear=\n|pastteams=\n* [[History of the Oakland Raiders|Los Angeles Raiders]] (1990\u20131994)\n* [[St. Louis Rams]] (1995\u20131996)\n|statlabel1=Games played\n|statvalue1=84\n|statlabel2= Games [[Starting lineup|started]]\n|statvalue2=4\n|statlabel3= [[Fumble]] recoveries\n|statvalue3=2\n|statlabel4= [[Interception]]s\n|statvalue4=3\n|statlabel5=[[Touchdown]]s\n|statvalue5=\n|nfl=DOR155733\n|pfr=DornTo20\n}}\n\n'''Torin Damon Dorn Sr.''' (born February 29, 1968) is a former professional [[American football]] [[cornerback]] in the  [[National Football League]]. He played seven seasons for the [[History of the Oakland Raiders|Los Angeles Raiders]] (1990\u20131994) and the [[St. Louis Rams]] (1995\u20131996). Dorn Sr. played college football for [[University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill]] from 1986-1989 where he played both running back and defensive back.\n\nHis son Torin Dorn Jr. plays [[basketball]] for the [[NC State Wolfpack men's basketball team]] after transferring from the [[UNC Charlotte 49ers men's basketball|Charlotte 49ers]] following his freshman season.<ref>{{cite web |title=Torin Dorn - 2017-18 - Men's Basketball |url=